Microsoft shares have fallen about 17% year-to-date on concerns over risks to its AI business and growing competition from Google's latest Gemini model ‌and Anthropic's Claude ⁠Cowork AI agent, wiping roughly $613 billion off its market value to about $2.98 trillion as ⁠of Friday. Amazon has shed around 13.85% so far this year, erasing about $343 billion in market value and leaving ​the company ​valued at roughly $2.13 trillion.
